parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling while driving can cause loss of control, accidents, and leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine suddenly shuts off while driving
without any warning or indication; the vehicle coasts to a stop
and can be restarted after a short time.

Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries, especially if the vehicle is traveling at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates on its own
regardless of the gear or speed; the engine RPM increases rapidly

5000 RPM); the acceleration pedal does not respond to input or becomes unresponsive; the vehicle may stall or almost stall before accelerating; pressing the brake may temporarily stop the acceleration

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of coil springs can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, and potentially catastrophic consequences if the spring breaks in the middle.
